
Onco Care Privacy Policy

Last updated: 11/27/2023

Welcome to Onco Care, a dedicated app designed to support and monitor cancer patients in their journey towards better health. Your privacy is important to us, and we are committed to protecting and respecting it. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and disclose personal information when you use our Onco Care app.

By using Onco Care, you agree to the terms outlined in this Privacy Policy. Please take a moment to read it carefully.

1. Information We Collect:

We collect information that is necessary for providing our services and enhancing your experience with Onco Care. This information may include:

Personal Information: Name, contact details, date of birth, and other relevant identification details.
Health Information: Medical history, treatment plans, medication details, and other health-related data.
Usage Information: Data on how you interact with the app, including log files, device information, and usage patterns.
2. How We Use Your Information:

We use the collected information to:

Provide and improve our services, including personalized health insights and recommendations.
Facilitate communication with your healthcare providers.
Analyze app usage to enhance user experience and optimize our services.
Ensure the security and integrity of the Onco Care app.
3. Data Sharing:

We may share your information with:

Healthcare Providers: To facilitate communication and collaboration in your healthcare journey.
Third-Party Service Providers: For essential services such as data storage, analysis, and customer support.
Legal Requirements: To comply with applicable laws, regulations, or legal processes.
4. Data Security:

We prioritize the security of your information and employ industry-standard measures to protect against unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, and destruction.

5. Your Choices:

You have the right to:

Access, update, or delete your personal information.
Opt-out of certain data processing activities.
Customize app settings according to your preferences.
6. Children's Privacy:

Onco Care is not intended for individuals under the age of 18. If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us, and we will take appropriate action.

7. Changes to the Privacy Policy:

We may update this Privacy Policy periodically to reflect changes in our practices or for legal reasons. We will notify you of any significant changes.

8. Contact Us:

If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding your privacy or this Privacy Policy, please contact us at [contact email].

Thank you for entrusting Onco Care with your healthcare journey.
